"{\"uid\": \"bangkokpost.com-opinion-opinion-2831268-end-wars-restore-olympic-peace\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"PUBLISHED : 18 Jul 2024 at 04:00 NEWSPAPER SECTION:Oped WRITER:Dmitry Muratov, Maria Ressa & Jody Williams There are at least 55 ongoingwarsaround the world.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 160, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"04:00 NEWSPAPER SECTION\", \"from\": 27, \"to\": 50}, {\"ngram\": \"Oped WRITER\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 62}, {\"ngram\": \"Dmitry Muratov\", \"from\": 63, \"to\": 77}, {\"ngram\": \"Maria Ressa\", \"from\": 79, \"to\": 90}, {\"ngram\": \"Jody Williams\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 106}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 156}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Politicians have consistently failed to end thearmed conflictsthat are ravaging their societies, and the dangers have been multiplied by the fact that local wars no longer remain local.\", \"from\": 161, \"to\": 346, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Politicians\", \"from\": 161, \"to\": 172}, {\"ngram\": \"conflictsthat\", \"from\": 214, \"to\": 227}, {\"ngram\": \"their societies\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 256}, {\"ngram\": \"the dangers\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 273}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 298, \"to\": 306}, {\"ngram\": \"local wars\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 322}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bloody conflict between Russia and Ukraine -- the biggest war on the European continent since 1945 -- has entered its third year and is still reverberating worldwide.\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 376, \"end\": 382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9998917479290725, \"rank\": 9.836542019990059e-05, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 387, \"end\": 394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9987843938821666, \"rank\": 0.0012169881852815807, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bloody conflict\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 367}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest war\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"the European continent\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 439}, {\"ngram\": \"its third year\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The spillover effects have included increased famine in Africa, a migration crisis in Europe, and the release of harmful substances into water, food, and milk supplies that ultimately reach people on six continents.\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 734, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The spillover effects\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 540}, {\"ngram\": \"increased famine\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 571}, {\"ngram\": \"Africa\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 581}, {\"ngram\": \"a migration crisis\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 601}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"the release\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 628}, {\"ngram\": \"harmful substances\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 661}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 667}, {\"ngram\": \"milk supplies\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 686}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 715}, {\"ngram\": \"six continents\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 733}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the end of this year, the number of people killed and injured as a result of the war in Ukraine is expected to exceed one million -- a casualty toll not seen in Europe since World War II.\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 826, \"end\": 833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9987843938821666, \"rank\": 0.0012169881852815807, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"this year\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 760, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 780}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 811}, {\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 822}, {\"ngram\": \"a casualty toll\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 886}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"World War II\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 924}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Gaza, where war has raged since last October, the United Nations puts the death toll as of January at 25,000 -- but the number may well be much higher.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 930, \"end\": 934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.7989952819233229, \"rank\": 0.25157184607234445, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 980, \"end\": 994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 0.9999999999240572, \"rank\": 7.581601965619913e-11, \"text\": \"United Nations\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 945}, {\"ngram\": \"last October\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"the death toll\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1014}, {\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1028}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1056}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And in Yemen, the UN says that 377,000 have died in the fighting or from disease over the past decade of civil war.\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1089, \"end\": 1094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yemen\", \"score\": 0.9999999995879989, \"rank\": 4.1149386994184327e-10, \"text\": \"Yemen\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yemen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yemen\"}, {\"begin\": 1100, \"end\": 1102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 0.9999999927072167, \"rank\": 6.086996932338478e-09, \"text\": \"UN\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the fighting\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"disease\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1162}, {\"ngram\": \"the past decade\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1183}, {\"ngram\": \"civil war\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1196}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As these and other conflicts rage, defence budgets around the world are expanding substantially; and hanging over it all is the threat -- repeated again and again in Ukraine -- of nuclear war.\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1365, \"end\": 1372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9987843938821666, \"rank\": 0.0012169881852815807, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"defence budgets\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1266}, {\"ngram\": \"the threat\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1333}, {\"ngram\": \"nuclear war\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The resources being mobilised are comparable to those needed to address climate change, or to eliminate hunger globally for the next 80 years.\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1534, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The resources\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1405}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1478}, {\"ngram\": \"hunger\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"the next 80 years\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1533}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just think about that: No one would go hungry or die of exhaustion, and no child would be undernourished, if the money now being spent on weaponry and soldiers was instead used to better the lives of the world's poor.\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1753, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No one\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1565}, {\"ngram\": \"exhaustion\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1602}, {\"ngram\": \"no child\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1616}, {\"ngram\": \"the money\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1654}, {\"ngram\": \"weaponry\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1682}, {\"ngram\": \"soldiers\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1695}, {\"ngram\": \"the lives\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of sustaining life, resources are being wasted on spreading death.\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1828, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1780}, {\"ngram\": \"resources\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1791}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1827}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The victims of today's wars are mostly people between the ages of 30 and 40, meaning that each death represents approximately half a life that could have been.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1989, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The victims\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1841}, {\"ngram\": \"today's wars\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1857}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1875}, {\"ngram\": \"the ages\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1892}, {\"ngram\": \"each death\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1930}, {\"ngram\": \"approximately half a life\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1967}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every 100,000 people killed is another four million years not lived.\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2058, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Every 100,000 people\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2010}, {\"ngram\": \"another four million years\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2047}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Consider all the breakthrough discoveries that will not be made, the children who will not be born, and the orphans who will suffer alone.\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2197, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all the breakthrough discoveries\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2100}, {\"ngram\": \"the children\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2136}, {\"ngram\": \"the orphans\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2174}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are not representatives of states.\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2236, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"representatives\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2225}, {\"ngram\": \"states\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2235}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But if the efforts of states to establish peace are not sufficient, individuals -- no matter their work or their station in life -- must step up.\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2382, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the efforts\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2255}, {\"ngram\": \"states\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2284}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 2305, \"to\": 2316}, {\"ngram\": \"their work\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2340}, {\"ngram\": \"their station\", \"from\": 2344, \"to\": 2357}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2365}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world must confront today's wars with one voice.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2435, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The world\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2392}, {\"ngram\": \"today's wars\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2419}, {\"ngram\": \"one voice\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is why we are asking His Holiness Pope Francis, His Holiness the Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew, His Holiness the Dalai Lama XIV, and Muslim and Jewish leaders to use their moral authority to appeal to all citizens of the world and to their governments.\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2475, \"end\": 2487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pope Francis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\"}, {\"begin\": 2557, \"end\": 2567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalai_Lama\", \"score\": 0.8992539242533064, \"rank\": 0.11203295592819083, \"text\": \"Dalai Lama\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalai_Lama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dalai_Lama\"}, {\"begin\": 2577, \"end\": 2583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9917700119395951, \"rank\": 0.008291438086671817, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}, {\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"score\": 0.9866124560767366, \"rank\": 0.013518306334072644, \"text\": \"Jewish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His Holiness\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2501}, {\"ngram\": \"the Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2538}, {\"ngram\": \"His Holiness\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2552}, {\"ngram\": \"their moral authority\", \"from\": 2610, \"to\": 2631}, {\"ngram\": \"all citizens\", \"from\": 2645, \"to\": 2657}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2670}, {\"ngram\": \"their governments\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2695}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Summer Olympic Games in Paris is an ideal opportunity to do this.\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2731, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998918638143, \"rank\": 1.0813622269999246e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 2024 Summer Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2727}, {\"ngram\": \"an ideal opportunity\", \"from\": 2740, \"to\": 2760}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the ancient Olympic Games, the frequent wars between the Greek city-states were suspended.\", \"from\": 2773, \"to\": 2870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2837, \"end\": 2854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polis\", \"score\": 0.9735148417218009, \"rank\": 0.026421854586018267, \"text\": \"Greek city-states\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ancient Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2780, \"to\": 2805}, {\"ngram\": \"the frequent wars\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 2824}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competition would take place between athletes in search of excellence.\", \"from\": 2871, \"to\": 2941, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Competition\", \"from\": 2871, \"to\": 2882}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 2899}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2908, \"to\": 2916}, {\"ngram\": \"search\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 2926}, {\"ngram\": \"excellence\", \"from\": 2930, \"to\": 2940}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We hope the billions of people who watch the Paris Games will follow this example and join with the world's religious and moral leaders in calling for peace.\", \"from\": 2942, \"to\": 3099, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the billions\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 2962}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 2972}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 2983, \"to\": 2998}, {\"ngram\": \"this example\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3023}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's religious and moral leaders\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3077}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 3093, \"to\": 3098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The conflicts in Ukraine, Gaza, and elsewhere call for an immediate ceasefire, followed by the exchange of all prisoners, the release of hostages, the return of human remains, and a start of negotiations.\", \"from\": 3101, \"to\": 3305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3118, \"end\": 3125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9987843938821666, \"rank\": 0.0012169881852815807, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 3127, \"end\": 3131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.7989952819233229, \"rank\": 0.25157184607234445, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The conflicts\", \"from\": 3101, \"to\": 3114}, {\"ngram\": \"elsewhere call\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3151}, {\"ngram\": \"an immediate ceasefire\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3178}, {\"ngram\": \"the exchange\", \"from\": 3192, \"to\": 3204}, {\"ngram\": \"all prisoners\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3221}, {\"ngram\": \"the release\", \"from\": 3223, \"to\": 3234}, {\"ngram\": \"hostages\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3246}, {\"ngram\": \"the return\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3258}, {\"ngram\": \"human remains\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3275}, {\"ngram\": \"a start\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3288}, {\"ngram\": \"negotiations\", \"from\": 3292, \"to\": 3304}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Our primary duty as adults is to ensure that our children survive us.\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3376, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Our primary duty\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3323}, {\"ngram\": \"adults\", \"from\": 3327, \"to\": 3333}, {\"ngram\": \"our children\", \"from\": 3352, \"to\": 3364}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3375}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of destroying each other and our societies with violence, let us devote our energies and resources to saving our planet.\", \"from\": 3377, \"to\": 3505, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our societies\", \"from\": 3414, \"to\": 3427}, {\"ngram\": \"violence\", \"from\": 3433, \"to\": 3441}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3449}, {\"ngram\": \"our energies\", \"from\": 3457, \"to\": 3469}, {\"ngram\": \"resources\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3483}, {\"ngram\": \"our planet\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us begin by reviving the Olympic peace.\\u00a92024 Project Syndicate Dmitry Muratov, Co-Founder, Publisher, and former editor-in-chief of Novaya Gazeta, won the Nobel Peace Prize in 2021.\", \"from\": 3506, \"to\": 3692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3555, \"end\": 3572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Syndicate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Project Syndicate\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Syndicate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Syndicate\"}, {\"begin\": 3574, \"end\": 3588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dmitry_Muratov\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dmitry Muratov\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dmitry_Muratov\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dmitry_Muratov\"}, {\"begin\": 3643, \"end\": 3656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novaya_Gazeta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novaya Gazeta\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novaya_Gazeta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novaya_Gazeta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3512}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic peace.\", \"from\": 3531, \"to\": 3549}, {\"ngram\": \"Co\", \"from\": 3589, \"to\": 3591}, {\"ngram\": \"Founder\", \"from\": 3592, \"to\": 3599}, {\"ngr